http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Michigan-varsity-invites-KCR/article13987726.ece

The University of Michigan (UoM), United States, has invited Chief Minister K. Chandrasekhar Rao and his colleagues T. Harish Rao, K.T. Rama Rao, Pocharam Srinivas Reddy and E. Rajender to visit its campus at Ann Arbor in Michigan during January 25 and February 15. In a recent letter addressed to the Chief Minister and copies marked to the other ministers, UoM Vice Provost for Global and Engaged Education James P. Holloway thanked the State Government for partnering the university student in “De-silting Irrigation Tanks in South India: The Sustainability of Decentralised Resource Distribution and Big Data + Small Farmers: Leveraging Data Science to inform Best Farming Practices in India in line with Mission Kakatiya.”“The UoM research activities range from medical to social to cultural,” he said.